text: Alexandrovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Alginsky Selsoviet, Davlekanovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 233 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 21 km from Davlekanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Davlekanovsky District
title: Alexandrovka, Davlekanovsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
